![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/4718c74f-5b4d-4676-abe4-da98d36e7c31/20240404_122409.jpg?format=original)

In a recent interview on Fox News Digital, Cody Rhodes, offered his perspective on the current state of WWE, dubbing it the "Renaissance Era." This term, laden with historical connotations of cultural and artistic revival, paints a picture of a period of growth and transformation within the wrestling industry.

**_“I’ve heard it coined as the Renaissance Era, and I really like that outlook on it,_**

**_For me, as a wrestler, I’m most excited that we no longer have to stand in the shadow of the Attitude Era because of the last two years we’ve done better business than they ever did”_**

Rhodes expressed his enthusiasm for this new era, highlighting a sense of liberation from the long-standing shadow of the Attitude Era. During the Attitude Era, which spanned the late 1990s to the early 2000s, WWE experienced unprecedented success and popularity, setting a high bar for subsequent generations of wrestlers. However, Rhodes contends that the current landscape of WWE has surpassed even those illustrious heights.

The wrestler-turned-executive-turned-wrestler pointed to the remarkable business performance of WWE in recent years as evidence of this newfound success.

According to Rhodes, WWE's achievements over the past two years have eclipsed those of the Attitude Era, signaling a shift in the dynamics of the industry.

This assertion underscores the significance of the ongoing changes and developments within WWE, indicating a departure from the established norms and a forging of new pathways forward.

Rhodes' characterization of the current era as a "Renaissance" implies not only a resurgence of interest and innovation but also a redefinition of wrestling's cultural relevance in contemporary society.

This sentiment resonates with fans and industry insiders alike, who recognize the evolving nature of professional wrestling and its enduring ability to captivate audiences worldwide.

As WWE continues to navigate the ever-changing landscape of sports entertainment, Rhodes' perspective offers a compelling glimpse into the aspirations and ambitions driving this transformative period in the industry's history. The "Renaissance Era" beckons, promising an exciting journey filled with boundless potential and untold possibilities for wrestlers and fans alike.